/*
this goes for a function that takes an integer array of any length (possibly a max length), and startPositionCoordinates, to place a tile-grid and fill it with glyphs, according to the array. and then doing only 1 pass per array|tile, to allow offsets of strings of with overlapping tiling (and overlapping glyphs).
*/

/*
way too many people use glyphs, either bitmap glyphs 
... or iChannel0 "font1" from otaviogood
... WITHOUT utilizing any tiling.

not using tiles means, every fragment checks for EVERY glyph anywhere, 
... with almost all of them being "out of frame|range"
using tiled glyphs, means the tile frames the glyph
... and every fragment only checks its brightness on ONE glyph.

tiled glyphs can be done with multiple passes, offset and scaled, 
...with different "strings" of glyphs for each tile
To allow for offset or overlapping or "dancing" glyphs (as in Undertale)
... you need oversized and overlapping tiles similar to
... https://www.shadertoy.com/view/Xt23zG

both parents have different issues due to bilinear interpolation of mipmaps,
... or for lacking mipmapping.
*/

